---
import { ViewTransitions } from 'astro:transitions';
import Paginated from '../components/Paginated.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <meta name="description" content="Install reasoningtool and start using it." />
  <title>Getting Started — reasoningtool</title>
  <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
  <ViewTransitions />
</head>
<body>
  <Paginated>
    <section>
      <h1>Getting started</h1>

      <div class="callout" style="border-left-color: var(--color-warning, #e0a800);">
        <p><strong>Use a skill before planning.</strong> Claude Code's built-in plan mode generates a single approach and commits to it immediately.
        If the problem space hasn't been mapped first, the resulting plan often misses better alternatives.</p>
        <p>Before asking Claude to plan or build, run a skill that surfaces the options:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><code>/decide</code> or <code>/dcp</code> &mdash; compare approaches before committing</li>
          <li><code>/search</code> or <code>/se</code> &mdash; map the full solution space</li>
          <li><code>/araw</code> &mdash; stress-test an approach from both sides</li>
          <li><code>/foht</code> &mdash; find methods when you know the goal but not how</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Installation</h2>

      <div class="card-grid card-grid--2">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Option 1: Run from the repo</h3>
          <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/benjam3n/reasoningtool.git
cd reasoningtool/claude-code-plugin
claude</code></pre>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h3>Option 2: Copy into your project</h3>
          <pre><code>cp -r path/to/reasoningtool/claude-code-plugin/skills your-project/
cp path/to/reasoningtool/claude-code-plugin/CLAUDE.md your-project/
cd your-project
claude</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Examples</h2>
      <pre><code>/araw should I change careers

/se what are all the ways I could approach this product launch

/aex we need to hire 3 more engineers by Q2

/cmp React vs Svelte for this project

/rca our deploy pipeline keeps failing

/uaua 4x what's the best approach to learning math</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Which skill to use</h2>

      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>You have&hellip;</th><th>Use</th><th>What it does</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>A claim to test</td><td><code>/claim</code></td><td>ARAW tests both sides</td></tr>
          <tr><td>A decision to make</td><td><code>/decide</code></td><td>Compares options, tests with ARAW</td></tr>
          <tr><td>An idea or proposal</td><td><code>/viability</code></td><td>Tests viability with ARAW</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Work to assess</td><td><code>/evaluate</code></td><td>Checks correctness, completeness, risks</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Something broken</td><td><code>/diagnose</code></td><td>Maps causes with UAUA, then tests each</td></tr>
          <tr><td>A space to explore</td><td><code>/search</code></td><td>Explores with UAUA, then tests findings</td></tr>
          <tr><td>A &ldquo;how do I&rdquo; question</td><td><code>/how</code></td><td>Finds methods (AR-forward)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>A goal or want</td><td><code>/want</code></td><td>Traces commitments (AR-forward)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>A feeling or frustration</td><td><code>/emotion</code></td><td>Acknowledges, then routes to what you need</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Something to execute</td><td><code>/action</code></td><td>Plans and executes steps</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Content to produce</td><td><code>/create</code></td><td>Routes to writing skills</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Need maximum effort</td><td><code>/certainty</code></td><td>Iterates until thoroughly resolved</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Something to improve</td><td><code>/iterate</code></td><td>Finds what to iterate, at what level, then does it</td></tr>
          <tr><td>A domain-specific question</td><td><code>/technical</code></td><td>Routes to specialized skills by domain</td></tr>
          <tr><td>A problem to analyze</td><td><code>/analyze</code></td><td>Routes to decomposition, systems analysis, or synthesis</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Need orientation</td><td><code>/meta</code></td><td>Skill discovery and usage guidance</td></tr>
          <tr><td>A prompt to improve</td><td><code>/sp</code></td><td>Adds precision, scope, and criteria before answering</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <pre><code>What do you have?
├── A statement → Is it testable?
│   ├── YES → /claim
│   └── It's more of an idea → /viability
├── A question → What kind?
│   ├── "Should I?" → /decide
│   ├── "How do I?" → /how
│   ├── "Why is this?" → /diagnose
│   └── "What are the options?" → /search
├── A goal → /want
├── A feeling → /emotion
├── Work to review → /evaluate
├── Something to do → /action
├── Content to write → /create
├── A technical question → /technical
├── Need analysis → /analyze
├── A prompt to improve → /sp
└── Not sure → /meta</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Depth scaling</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Example</th><th>What you get</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>/araw claim</code></td><td>Default (2x) &mdash; 4&ndash;5 tree levels, 20+ findings</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>/araw 4x claim</code></td><td>5&ndash;6 levels, 35+ findings, edge cases</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>/araw 8x claim</code></td><td>6&ndash;8 levels, 55+ findings</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>/uaua 4x topic</code></td><td>Alternating search at 4x depth</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>/rca 4x symptom</code></td><td>5+ causal chains, 7 why-levels deep</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>/se 4x space</code></td><td>35+ items, 7 dimensions, 6 edge cases</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>/fwa 4x answer</code></td><td>8 checks, 4 alternatives, 3 sources</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>Depth scaling is supported by 40+ analytical skills including <code>/araw</code>, <code>/ar</code>, <code>/aw</code>, <code>/uaua</code>, <code>/foht</code>, <code>/se</code>, <code>/dd</code>, <code>/rca</code>, <code>/ht</code>, <code>/fwa</code>, <code>/sdc</code>, <code>/fohw</code>, <code>/insd</code>, and more.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Python tools</h2>
      <pre><code>pip install openai pyyaml
export OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-your-key"
cd src/araw

python auto_expand_llm.py --db career.db --seed "Should I start a business?"
python visualize.py --db career.db --serve</code></pre>
      <p><a href="/tools">Full tool documentation &rarr;</a></p>
    </section>
  </Paginated>
</body>
</html>
